{
  "__inputs": [
    {
      "name": "DS_PROMETHEUS",
      "label": "Prometheus",
      "description": "",
      "type": "datasource",
      "pluginId": "prometheus",
      "pluginName": "Prometheus"
    },
    {
      "name": "DS_LOKI",
      "label": "Loki",
      "description": "",
      "type": "datasource",
      "pluginId": "loki",
      "pluginName": "Loki"
    }
  ],
  "__requires": [
    {
      "type": "datasource",
      "id": "prometheus",
      "name": "Prometheus",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    },
    {
      "type": "datasource",
      "id": "loki",
      "name": "Loki",
      "version": "1.0.0"
    }
  ],
  "annotations": {
    "list": []
  },
  "description": "Garden P2P bridge health — vdhptp01 (house) ↔ vdhptp02 (garden), NanoStation 5AC airOS 8.7.22. Story: is the wireless link to the back garden OK? Six panels answer signal quality, link health, and throughput from SNMP data scraped every 60s via snmp_exporter ubiquiti_airmax module. Reliable metrics: ubntRadioSignal, ubntRadioCcq, ifInOctets/ifOutOctets on ath0. Syslog panel shows no data until airOS syslog destination is pointed at 172.16.2.235:514.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "title": "Bridge Status",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: is the bridge reachable right now? Green = both vdhptp01 and vdhptp02 responded to SNMP in the last 2 minutes (snmp_scrape_duration_seconds > 0). Red = one or both devices are not responding. Query: count(snmp_scrape_duration_seconds{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"} > 0).",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "orange",
                "value": 1
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 2
              }
            ]
          },
          "mappings": [
            {
              "type": "value",
              "options": {
                "1": {
                  "text": "ONE DEVICE DOWN",
                  "color": "orange",
                  "index": 0
                },
                "2": {
                  "text": "BOTH UP",
                  "color": "green",
                  "index": 1
                },
                "0": {
                  "text": "BRIDGE DOWN",
                  "color": "red",
                  "index": 2
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "unit": "short"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "none",
        "justifyMode": "center",
        "orientation": "horizontal",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "count(snmp_scrape_duration_seconds{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"} > 0)",
          "legendFormat": "Devices UP",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Bridge SNMP Reachability",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: how strong is the signal on each end of the bridge right now? ubntRadioSignal in dBm. For a short garden link this should be above -65 dBm. Green > -65, yellow -65 to -75, red < -75. vdhptp01 = house side, vdhptp02 = garden side.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": -75
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": -65
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "dBm",
          "mappings": [],
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.device}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 9,
        "x": 6,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 3,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "sparkline",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "horizontal",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value_and_name"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "ubntRadioSignal{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Signal Strength Now (dBm)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: how good is the link quality on each end right now? ubntRadioCcq = Client Connection Quality, 0–100. Higher is better. 100 = perfect; < 50 = marginal. Green > 75, yellow 50-75, red < 50.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "red",
                "value": null
              },
              {
                "color": "yellow",
                "value": 50
              },
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": 75
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "percent",
          "max": 100,
          "min": 0,
          "mappings": [],
          "displayName": "${__field.labels.device}"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 9,
        "x": 15,
        "y": 1
      },
      "id": 4,
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "background",
        "graphMode": "sparkline",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "horizontal",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": ["lastNotNull"],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value_and_name"
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "ubntRadioCcq{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}}",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "CCQ — Link Quality Now (%)",
      "type": "stat"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 5
      },
      "id": 10,
      "title": "Trends",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: has the signal been stable over the last 6 hours? ubntRadioSignal from SNMP, sampled every 60s. A flat line near -60 dBm is ideal. Sudden drops or large swings indicate interference or physical obstruction. Dashed threshold lines at -65 (green/yellow boundary) and -75 (yellow/red boundary).",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never",
            "spanNulls": true
          },
          "unit": "dBm",
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {"color": "red", "value": null},
              {"color": "yellow", "value": -75},
              {"color": "green", "value": -65}
            ]
          },
          "mappings": []
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 6
      },
      "id": 5,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "ubntRadioSignal{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}} signal",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Signal Strength — 6h Trend (dBm)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: has CCQ been stable over the last 6 hours? ubntRadioCcq sampled every 60s. Consistent values near 40 on this short garden link are acceptable; sustained drops below 30 indicate link problems.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 2,
            "fillOpacity": 10,
            "showPoints": "never",
            "spanNulls": true
          },
          "unit": "percent",
          "max": 100,
          "min": 0,
          "mappings": []
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 12,
        "x": 12,
        "y": 6
      },
      "id": 6,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "ubntRadioCcq{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}} CCQ",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "CCQ — Link Quality 6h Trend (%)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: is real traffic flowing across the bridge? Rate of bytes on ath0 (the wireless interface) over the last 24 hours. Uses ifInOctets + ifOutOctets from IF-MIB, converted to bits/second. Both devices should show symmetric-ish traffic: what vdhptp01 TX's, vdhptp02 RX's. Uses $__rate_interval for correct handling across zoom levels.",
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "palette-classic"
          },
          "custom": {
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "fillOpacity": 20,
            "showPoints": "never",
            "spanNulls": true,
            "stacking": {
              "mode": "none",
              "group": "A"
            }
          },
          "unit": "bps",
          "mappings": []
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 13
      },
      "id": 7,
      "options": {
        "legend": {
          "displayMode": "list",
          "placement": "bottom"
        },
        "tooltip": {
          "mode": "multi"
        }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "rate(ifInOctets{ifDescr=\"ath0\",device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}[$__rate_interval]) * 8",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}} RX",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "expr": "rate(ifOutOctets{ifDescr=\"ath0\",device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}[$__rate_interval]) * 8",
          "legendFormat": "{{device}} TX",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Throughput — ath0 TX/RX 24h (bits/s)",
      "type": "timeseries"
    },
    {
      "collapsed": false,
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 1,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 20
      },
      "id": 11,
      "title": "Syslog",
      "type": "row"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "loki",
        "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
      },
      "description": "Answers: what events has the bridge logged in the last hour? Requires airOS syslog destination configured to 172.16.2.235:514 (Vector LoadBalancer). Currently shows no data — the UDP/514 pipeline is in place (Vector airmax_normalize transform, device label mapped from source IP) but the NanoStation syslog output has not yet been pointed at the cluster. See chg-2026-05-26-009 follow-ups.",
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 8,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 21
      },
      "id": 8,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": false,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "loki",
            "uid": "${DS_LOKI}"
          },
          "expr": "{device=~\"vdhptp.+\"}",
          "legendFormat": "",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Bridge Syslog — last 1h (⚠ no data until airOS syslog is pointed at 172.16.2.235:514)",
      "type": "logs"
    }
  ],
  "refresh": "1m",
  "schemaVersion": 38,
  "tags": ["network", "airmax", "bridge", "garden"],
  "time": {
    "from": "now-6h",
    "to": "now"
  },
  "timepicker": {},
  "timezone": "browser",
  "title": "Garden P2P Bridge",
  "uid": "garden-bridge-v1",
  "version": 1
}
